                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the <placeName>Holy City</placeName> by <persName>Titus</persName>?</p>\n            <p>II—If so, were these other hymns of praise<lb/> taken exclusively from the canonical\n                scrip-<lb/>tures or not?</p>\n            <p>III—Does the three-fold distinction laid down<lb/> by <persName>Paul</persName> in\n                his Epistle to Colossians II. 16.<lb/> and to the Ephesians V.19. refer to any\n                recog-<lb/>nized division or arrangement of the Book<lb/> of Psalms, or is it a\n                general description of the<lb/> species of sacred poetry in current use at that<lb/>\n                time?</p>\n            <p>IV. If there were in use hymns of praise<lb/> not to be found in the canonical\n                scriptures<lb/> are they still extant, and can you refer us to<lb/> any work easily\n                obtained which contains<lb/> either them, or any information on the<lb/>\n                subject.</p>\n            <p>V. Was the entire Book of Psalms used in<lb/> the ancient temple or synagogue\n                service<lb/> and if not, what part <hi rend=\"underline\">was</hi> used?</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">We are very sorry to trouble you<lb/> with such a long list of\n                queries, but<lb/> hope that you will have it in your power<lb/> to give us an answer\n                at an early</p>"
                  },
